This is a small but vibrant trading post.
This trading post has grown into a large town, offering more protection against raiders and brigands and thus attracting more merchants who prefer to stay here and trade.

This is a major trading hub, where merchants come from all directions to trade their wares. All goods and services known to civilized man can be found here, and a myriad of languages echo through the many streets and alleys

In this Manufactory Shiliujian, or pomegranate arrows, are produced and shipped to the campaining archers across the empire. Pomegranate Arrows were the first large scale weaponized use of gunpowder and would deliver an explosion or start combustion.

In this Manufactory Huoqiang, or fire lances, are produced and men trained to wield this inovative weapon. Fire lances were a gunpowder weapon and the ancestor of modern firearms originally consisting of a lance with a tube attached capable of firing a single or doble shot before engaging in melee combat.

In this gunnery Tuhuoqiang, or handguns, are produced and men trained to wield this inovative weapon. Fire-emitting lances were the first proper gunpowder weapons. Improving on the previous design they were cabable of firing bullets in stead of schrapnell and were used primarly at the distance.

In this foundry Pao, or cannons, are produced and men trained to wield this inovative weapon. Handcannons were larger versions of the handgun. In Asia they were mostly used as anti-personnel weapons and were later reffined to might potency by Europeans and Middle-easterns.

In this manufactory Huojian, or fire arrows, are produced and men trained to wield this inovative weapon. Fire arrows are the precursors of modern rockets and varied in size with the earliest being shot from bows later evolging into strange contraptions capable of firing hundreds of them at once or into impactfull missiles with several hundred meters of destructive radius.

The Aj X Bhak(Count of Captives) were proven warriors and would be adressed by the number of enemies they had taken captive prefixed on their title. Ex: A Winak Bhak(Taker of 20 prisioners)
The lack of obsidian supplies required for the creation of weapons readily available in the Tarascan homelands created the stimulous for the mastery over cooper.
The fearless warriors of the Otomi order are trained here. They represent the elite of the Otomi war machine and entire armies have known to rout after earing the sound of their death whistles.
The fearsome Chichimecas muster in anticipation of profitable incursions into the rich mesoamerican neighbours.
